Also, a list of requirements for these documents.
To date, the law "On the procurement of goods, works, services by individual types of legal entities" regulates the procurement activities of individual types of legal entities.
The requirements for the content, form, presentation and composition of the application for participation in the procurement are set by the customers themselves in the procurement documentation.
"As a result, the customers set excessive requirements for content, the submission of an application, the mandatory presence in its composition of certificates, certificates, excerpts, the period of receipt of which in the authorised bodies of the procurement is comparable to the time of submission of applications, which does not lead to such a vehicle.
The new bill provides for the establishment of a comprehensive list of documents that customers have the right to request in the form of an application from the participants in the procurement who are subjects of small and medium-sized enterprises.
"The adoption of the document will exclude the arbitrary establishment by customers of requirements for the composition and content of applications of participants subject to small and medium-sized enterprises," - says the explanatory note.
